From: Spencer Garnets <s.garnets17@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH 2/2] mirror (Bfloat16 act + E2m1 weight) relaxation in is_trtllm_moe_supported

Companion to 0001-relax-bf16-act-e2m1-weight.patch.

The python guard flashinfer/fused_moe/core.py:is_trtllm_moe_supported()
rejects (Bfloat16 act + E2m1 weight) in symmetry with the C++ launcher
check_moe(). Relaxing the C++ side without the python guard would still
fall through to a dispatch-time return False; both must relax.

Apply against:
  /usr/local/lib/python3.12/dist-packages/flashinfer/fused_moe/core.py

---
diff --git a/flashinfer/fused_moe/core.py b/flashinfer/fused_moe/core.py
index df6e92d..bf6ddf9 100644
--- a/flashinfer/fused_moe/core.py
+++ b/flashinfer/fused_moe/core.py
@@ -119,7 +119,14 @@ def is_trtllm_moe_supported(
         return False
     if dtype_weights == DtypeTrtllmGen.E4m3 and dtype_act != DtypeTrtllmGen.E4m3:
         return False
-    if dtype_weights == DtypeTrtllmGen.E2m1 and dtype_act != DtypeTrtllmGen.E2m1:
+    # ai-blaise #15 iter7: E2m1 weights now accept BOTH E2m1 act (host-side
+    # pre-quantize path) and Bfloat16 act (in-cubin fused SF-generation
+    # path; eliminates the scaled_fp4_quant_linear host call for
+    # DSv3.2-REAP). Mirrors the C++ launcher check_moe() relaxation.
+    if dtype_weights == DtypeTrtllmGen.E2m1 and dtype_act not in [
+        DtypeTrtllmGen.E2m1,
+        DtypeTrtllmGen.Bfloat16,
+    ]:
         return False
     if dtype_weights == DtypeTrtllmGen.MxE2m1 and dtype_act not in [
         DtypeTrtllmGen.MxE2m1,
